cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM. 

This paper deals with answer-set programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses graph representations of programs, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The concept of backdoors is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and the paper establishes new hardness results. The paper also discusses the parity of negative edges on bad cycles, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper deals with tractable target classes, which is related to data structures (cs.DS).
